{"id": 214, "title": "Ticket #214: GitTrac doesn't allow wiki pages with two capital letters in a row.", "description": "<blockquote>\n<span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=GitTrac\" title=\"Git Trac\">GitTrac</a></span> doesn't allow wiki pages with two capital letters in a row.  This might be okay, but the failure case is really annoying.\n\n<p>Examples:\n\n</p><p></p><ul>\n<li>HowToAddATest - Invalid\n</li><li><span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=HowToAddaTest\" title=\"How To Adda Test\">HowToAddaTest</a></span> - Valid\n</li><li>PortingToFreeBSD - Invalid\n</li><li><span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=PortingToFreeBsd\" title=\"Porting To Free Bsd\">PortingToFreeBsd</a></span> - Valid\n</li></ul>\n\n<p>You'll note that the invalid entries aren't links at all.  This is okay.  But if you use the wiki link to give different text:\n\n</p><p></p><ul>\n<li><span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=HowToAddATest\" title=\"How To Add A Test\">How To Add A Test</a></span> - Invalid\n</li><li><span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=HowToAddaTest\" title=\"How To Adda Test\">How TO Add a Test</a></span>- Valid\n</li><li><span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=PortingToFreeBSD\" title=\"Porting To Free B S D\">Porting To FreeBSD</a></span> - Invalid\n</li><li><span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=PortingToFreeBsd\" title=\"Porting To Free Bsd\">Porting To FreeBsd</a></span> - Valid\n</li></ul>\n\n<p>Now links are generated.  This seems okay, except if you click on one of the invalid links, you end up on the front page.  It is not possible to create a page of the forbidden name.\n\n</p><p>Expected behavior:\n\n</p><p>Allow multiple capital letters in a row in a wiki page name.  Maybe it will be a little gross, as the title will \"Free B S D\", but it's better than simply not working.\n\n</p><p>Failing that, if I end up on <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=HowToAddATest\" title=\"How To Add A Test\">an invalid page name</a></span>, instead of seeing <span class=\"wiki\"><a href=\"wiki?p=WikiIndex\" title=\"Wiki Index\">WikiIndex</a></span>, I should get an error message.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2021-Sep-29 10:23</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/3fc39a8a60be59ec023208d5a72f6038da7f149c\">[64520]</a></span>: Merged <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/6851be2653fd451dadbadd897fcc1759404ec915\">[64485]</a></span>, <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/59698492b6cfacff256181373a28f05438a4cede\">[64486]</a></span>, <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/255386f65eaf7ef0321690101704a80f4c3c79b9\">[64508]</a></span>, <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/4da0e1a84f30f0d7d7dd3930d80d37cb2b6e51aa\">[64512]</a></span>, <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/f119872c1f8b4f39072e00a24c4453906226626e\">[64518]</a></span>, <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/c946db30867df7a85adb8a744c4134abf1f211ec\">[64519]</a></span>, Merge pull request <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"new\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=214\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('214'); return false;\" title=\"GitTrac doesn't allow wiki pages with two capital letters in a row.\">#214</a></span> from htcondor/V9_3-HTCONDOR-616-branch V9_3-HTCONDOR-616-branch Committer: <span class=\"wiki\"><a